Spatial composition analysis revealed that several of the domains were intercorrelated (
Fig.2h, S.Table6,7
). For example, two immune domains (RCN11 - T cells, RCN13 -B cells) showed a positive correlation with each other, as well as with the immune-infiltrated stroma (RCN02). In contrast, the immune-cold stroma displayed a negative correlation with these immune domains (
Fig.2h
). The cancer cell domains also revealed significant correlations with other spatial domains. For instance, the neighborhood of cancer idle phenotype (RCN01) was positively correlated with the immune-cold tumor-stromal interface (TSI), whereas the neighborhood of cancer cells displaying immunogenic phenotypes was negatively correlated with the immune-cold stroma (RCN01) (
Fig.2h
). These findings suggest that the spatial domains of the TME are functionally coordinated in HGSC.
